race.comment: LET IT BEEL (7) looks the one to beat. Two runs back from a spell have been good, sticking on well for fourth out to this trip at Sandown Hillside last start in a stronger maiden. Should be further improved off that and rates highly. Wary of FUTURE FRANKIE (9, a filly by Frankel out of a Deep Impact mare who debuts for the Mark Walker yard. She's won a jumpout and the stable kicking her off over a mile suggests she could be ready to go. ZA ZA BEST (8) was well fancied on debut at Geelong and just knocked up late over the 1440m to finish midfield. She'll be better for that and the rise in trip should only suit better. ILOVETHISTOWN (1) put in a better effort out to this trip last time and should get a nice run just off the pace. Each-way. SURPERB FROST (3) next best.
